ify whether that's actually missing or if it's been accounted for elsewhere.\n\nThe real question is what information matters most for answering user questions—if someone asks about the template's purpose or structure, they need the overview and directory contents, but the implementation details and review rules are secondary.\n\nI'll flag the missing 概要 and コンテンツ sections as minor omissions since they're introductory rather than critical for implementation. For s4, I'm checking against the hints and noticing that 単体テスト標準 is actually present, so that's accounted for.\n\nNow I'm compiling my final findings: six minor omissions across s1 and s4 covering missing section content, descriptions, and conditional recommendations, plus a hints_missing category to report. I'm settling on treating all the omissions as minor since none would lead to incorrect implementation guidance—they're mostly contextual background and setup instructions rather than substantive technical direction. Let me organize my final findings now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21549,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21549,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2415588c-d07c-4aa4-9a84-3937230c6a9c","uuid":"30788eba-c905-49be-b36a-be11cf1b0ca4"}
